<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.button {
  border: none;
  color: white;
  padding: 16px 32px;
  text-align: center;
  text-decoration: none;
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 16px;
  margin: 4px 2px;
  transition-duration: 0.4s;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.LSU {
  background-color: white; 
  color: black; 
  border: 4px solid #FDD023;
}

.LSU:hover {
  background-color: #461D7C;
  color: white;
}

.duke {
  background-color: white; 
  color: black; 
  border: 4px solid #012169;
}

.duke:hover {
  background-color: #012169;
  color: white;
}

</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>The button element - Styled with CSS</h1>

<h2>Use the :hover selector to change the style of the button when you move the mouse over it.</h2>

<h2><strong>Tip:</strong> Use the transition-duration property to determine the speed of the "hover" effect:</h2>

<h2 style="color: green;">Buttons change color on hover but don't do anything when clicked </h2>

<h2 style="color: purple;"> Another big game this friday, who you picking?</h2>
<button class="button LSU">LSU</button>
<button class="button duke">Duke</button>

</body>
</html>
